          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #3\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#296\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:176`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:179`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:199`\n\nWhen `get_detector(..., on_error=\"log_and_null\")` catches a build failure, it caches a `NullDetector` under the same cache key used by later `on_error=\"raise\"` calls.\n\nImpact:\n\n- A transient model download/OOM/build failure can make later fail-fast callers silently get no layout.\n- Unknown-key fallbacks can likewise hide later valid configuration.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Do not cache fallback detectors under normal success keys.\n- Include the fallback policy in the cache key, or make `on_error=\"raise\"` bypass cached fallbacks.\n- Add regression tests for failure-then-raise and unknown-key-then-register flows.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-24T10:37:08Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Shipped in cc965da (Merge 0ece369 on main): removed _DETECTOR_CACHE write in fallback exception handler so log_and_null wrappers are no longer cached; 3 new tests cover the behavior.",
