          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #3\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    get_detector(..., on_error='log_and_null') caches a NullDetector under the same key used by later fail-fast calls.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    A transient model build failure can make later on_error='raise' callers silently get no layout.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:176`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:179`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/registry.py:199`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Do not cache fallback detectors under normal success keys.\n- [ ] Include fallback policy in the cache key, or make on_error='raise' bypass cached fallbacks.\n- [ ] Add failure-then-raise regression tests.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:03:40Z",
